subSubSection.paragraph:
Description.
Female
(n = 1) Habitus: curled in on itself ventrally. Cuticle finely annulated, annule width 1 µm at mid-body. Lateral field 2 µm wide, marked with four incisures (
Fig. 1D
), middle two incisures faint. Head offset (
Fig. 1E
). Lip region 3 µm high and 6 µm broad. Stylet 10 µm long with basal swellings. Lumen of stylet distinct. Median bulb spherical to slightly rectangular (
Fig. 1E
). Valve distinct, situated slightly off centre in posterior half. Nerve ring situated 68 µm from anterior end, less than one corresponding body width from base of median bulb. Excretory pore 73 µm from anterior end, opposite posterior end of nerve ring (
Fig. 1E
). Ovary outstretched with a single row of oocytes (
Fig. 1F
& 
2E
). Spermatheca oval in shape containing sperm cells (
Fig. 2A
). Vulval lips slightly raised with the vagina occupying more than half the corresponding body width, curving slightly anteriorly (
Fig. 1G
). Post-vulval uterine sac 37 µm in length, about 2.5 times vulval body width and shorter than half the vulva-anus distance (
Fig. 1G
& 
2C
). Tail elongate conoid, 34 µm long. Terminus bearing slightly star-shaped mucro with central part more prominent (
Fig. 1C
& 
2B
).

Male
(n = 1): Habitus: curled in on itself ventrally. Head, lip region and pharynx as in female (
Fig. 1A
). Stylet 11 µm, longer than in female. Tail 32 µm long with three pairs of subventral papillae (
Fig. 1B
). Mucro similar to female but less star-shaped. Spicules rose-thorn shaped with well-developed apex (18 µm) and rostrum (11 µm), medially measuring 14 µm. Spicules with an anterior subventral concavity and swelling on dorsal limb (
Fig. 1B
& 
2D
).
